Subject   DMT Update

Steve,

We weren't sure if you were able to join this afternoon's call regarding Project Accelerate at 1:30pm PST.
Nonetheless, the meeting went well and the dial-in details are included below for the second call tomorrow
(10/26) that will specifically cover the Card Connect Term Sheet and the economics of DMT at 10:30am PST.

Jared,

I am working to schedule a follow up meeting to address any outstanding questions post DMT that come
from our discussion tomorrow morning.
To recap our discussion this afternoon, the acquisition of Card Connect will provide FDC with a gateway
and merchant acquiring platform. The gateway focus is crucial for ISVs, ERPs and VARs which are
becoming increasingly more important to payment processing.

As the below chart indicates, the ISO channel is expected to decline due to a combination of technology
obsolescence and the inability to compete in the current market. The ISO channel is currently 55% of FDC's
total business today and DMT will be a value-added offering to help combat some of the market shift.

DMT Entity:
-  DMT is 100% owned by Shift4 employees and does not have a separate evaluation.
-  DMT has several divisions, or lines or lines of business, that include Merchant Acquiring, SaaS
   Platforms, ISV's, VARs, and other.
-  The Merchant Acquiring piece of DMT encompasses the economics associated with payment
   processing and is the only item addressed by in the Card Connect Term Sheet.
- The existing Shift4 EBITDA multiple on DMT should provide the enterprise value for Card
   Connect

Tomorrow's call will begin promptly at 10:30am PST.
